Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.82,0:00:10.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't! It's a whalesquid! Leave it alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.19,0:00:29.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Targeting accuracy is lower \Ndue to undersea conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.46,0:00:30.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hit it with my next one!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:31.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:34.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If that thing gets riled up, \Nit'll become even more violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.61,0:00:38.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.59,0:00:43.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:48.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Charge next shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:52.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suggestion: Use of beam weapon \Nundersea is inefficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.19,0:00:54.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Possible damage to allied craft \Nhas also been taken into account.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.95,0:00:57.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.79,0:01:05.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.01,0:02:50.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,A Soldier's Fate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:03:00.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! Lookin' good!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.17,0:03:02.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off. I'm in no laughing mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.68,0:03:07.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, the alien flew \Nback in a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.31,0:03:11.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he did in a whalesquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:15.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.91,0:03:20.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,People have regarded whalesquids as \Nsacred creatures since ancient times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.03,0:03:23.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To murder one with no cause whatsoever...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.27,0:03:26.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, what are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.56,0:03:30.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The citizens are in shock \Nand it's spreading fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.97,0:03:35.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumors are even going around \Nthat this will bring on a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.49,0:03:37.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one that started all this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:41.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural for \Neveryone to be anxious...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.34,0:03:43.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:44.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.34,0:03:53.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's just superstition...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:56.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...to seafarers, it's the ultimate taboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.91,0:03:59.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope that nothing comes of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.94,0:04:11.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.91,0:04:17.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.33,0:04:21.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Estimate: Four hours for DNA \Namplification and analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:23.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.06,0:04:25.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:29.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, chances that results will differ from \Nthe intrinsic reaction analysis are small.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:31.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.52,0:04:34.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to find out if the Earth Hideauze \Nhave any unique characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.99,0:04:36.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.39,0:04:39.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hideauze have even invaded the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.66,0:04:50.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I have brought them here from space?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.73,0:04:54.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:04:57.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible to do a biological analysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.99,0:05:01.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I am unable to obtain information \Non their invasion strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.16,0:05:03.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll gather info from the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:06.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to know their total \Nnumbers and range of activities--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:07.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.08,0:05:24.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.15,0:05:26.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:31.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad these days, thanks to you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:39.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go easy on your official duties, and think \Nabout taking a vacation once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:42.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Move to the main ship, \Nwhich has a lot of green...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:44.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I like it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:48.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I may not be able to walk anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.43,0:05:53.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but these legs remember well \Njust how big this fleet is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:58.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,These eyes and ears remember \Nwhat kind of people are aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:04.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to keep protecting the smiles \Nand voices of the people who live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.53,0:06:08.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the proof that I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:12.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no match for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.98,0:06:15.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when you need to play it safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:19.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it seems the fleet has gotten \Ninvolved with a whalesquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:21.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:26.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how old I get, there \Nare always new experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.21,0:06:29.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying you're not afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:32.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what the reality of \Nthe situation is, accepting it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:35.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,is a privilege for those of us who are alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:37.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Privilege?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.82,0:06:40.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, if we can't see \Nit through to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:43.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,all we can do is entrust it to the young.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.51,0:06:46.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.96,0:06:50.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys must've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.42,0:06:54.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's treasure nobody else has \Nlooked for in whalesquid territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:59.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And we're gonna bring it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.28,0:07:02.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oodles of it! Barrels full!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.34,0:07:03.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.85,0:07:07.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody else would dare to dive into \Nthe middle of a whalesquid lair!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:08.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:12.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, who's confirmed \Nthat there's treasure in their nest?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.34,0:07:17.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is somebody who saw \Nit with his own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:20.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me... right before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:26.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We're repairmen, not salvagers!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.61,0:07:29.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what kind of idiot would be willing \Nto mix it up with a whalesquid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.91,0:07:32.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The idiot who owns that tin can!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:34.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With him on our side, even \Nmonsters are a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:38.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me they're \Nalready on board with this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For that... I need a little time...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.09,0:07:44.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! He hasn't \Neven made the arrangements?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.18,0:07:48.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll listen once you've actually got \NSpaceboy and the tin can lined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:50.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting adjourned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.09,0:07:54.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing?! You were with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.97,0:07:57.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you let him attack a whalesquid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:03.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the ship owners are concerned, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:06.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all of the requests I've gotten \Ndemanding that measures be taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:08.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't make any excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:11.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault for not warning \Nhim properly beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:16.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words... there \Nare many more of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:21.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case... I will carry out my \Nmission by continuing to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:25.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you... know what you're saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.72,0:08:30.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hideauze are a threat to the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:32.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A war of extermination is our only choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:35.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:39.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no reason to kill \Nthe whalesquids whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.27,0:08:45.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless the threat is eliminated \Ncompletely, there can be no true peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:48.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you right now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:50.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Gargantia, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.53,0:08:55.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fleet Commander would like \Na detailed briefing from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:08:57.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good timing. They're here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.18,0:09:01.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you have the Fleet Commander \Nhear you arguing with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.99,0:09:05.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's fine. I'll report to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:07.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You two can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:27.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Flange!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.20,0:09:31.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.61,0:09:48.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.45,0:09:51.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hideauze...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:54.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, tell me about the whalesquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:57.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How many are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.79,0:10:00.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is their combat strength? \NDo they have any weaknesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:03.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a second, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:07.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still mean to do something \Nto them? You better not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.39,0:10:11.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The whalesquid are terrifying \Ncreatures if you start something,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.10,0:10:13.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but they never attack unprovoked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.78,0:10:16.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Wouldn't you \Nfeel bad about killing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:18.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.48,0:10:20.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They are enemies that need to be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:22.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you understand that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:26.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After coming all the way to Earth, why \Nare you trying to continue your war?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't draw us into a conflict \Nthat has nothing to do with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.60,0:10:30.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, your civilization...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.07,0:10:35.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea what you're saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.70,0:10:41.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At present, your civilization is merely being \Nignored by the Hideauze because of its simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.15,0:10:45.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is only a matter of \Ntime before they strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.55,0:10:49.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, how \Nwill you people respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:50.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.28,0:10:54.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have specific measures been planned?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.21,0:10:57.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you people even have a vision \Nto develop your civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.80,0:11:02.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even think about that, but your \Nfellow humans are fighting right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.38,0:11:08.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is too late to act when \Nthe enemy shows hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.96,0:11:11.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will attack before that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:12.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:14.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't change your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:19.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I live to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:24.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to do that. \NLedo, you're your own person...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.93,0:11:38.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion, if you've got a funny \Nidea in mind, forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.85,0:11:40.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.18,0:11:45.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're thinking of using Ledo and Chamber \Nto go deep into whalesquid territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.72,0:11:51.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that? He's got a beef \Nwith the whalesquid anyway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:53.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's treasure at the bottom, I \Ncan just swoop down and grab it all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.81,0:11:56.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means putting the fleet in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.55,0:12:00.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what you dredge up, if it's not \Nuseful to Gargantia, it's meaningless!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.40,0:12:02.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it'll be useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.43,0:12:08.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talkin' about unexplored regions! \NTo find unheard-of treasures!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.40,0:12:12.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Join my team. It's \Ngotta get a salvager's blood racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.58,0:12:17.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I'm not interested in \Na little kid's expedition team.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:19.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:23.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna bring stuff up for the sake of \Nyour two-bit pride, so you can brag about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:29.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't dive yourself, so you use other people,\N and you're satisfied with that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:33.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellows, you wench!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:52.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I swore I'd get revenge \Nfor my big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.25,0:12:56.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just a dream, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.10,0:12:59.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How's the connection to the Alliance coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.31,0:13:01.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is still no response.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:03.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And our coordinates?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.69,0:13:09.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Analysis: Further parallax observation \Nof this planet's orbit is required.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:10.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.61,0:13:14.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Analysis of the biological \Nsample is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.96,0:13:16.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the result?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:20.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although the composition of the exoskeleton \Nhas adapted to the environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:24.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,there is no difference between the \Ngenetic makeup of this and the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.84,0:13:26.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed: They are identical species.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:27.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:31.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The policy of destruction isn't wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.48,0:13:34.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's necessary for the humans of Earth, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:37.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't they understand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.00,0:13:38.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.73,0:13:40.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to language analysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.77,0:13:43.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the definition of "survival strategy" \Nfor the human race of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.71,0:13:46.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,greatly differs from that of the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.95,0:13:48.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.56,0:13:53.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that question is not \Nin any standard Alliance dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.53,0:13:56.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, it exists in Earth language.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.70,0:13:57.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.55,0:14:00.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Co-existence and co-prosperity".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:11.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea galaxy is active!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.70,0:14:13.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen anything like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.55,0:14:14.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.47,0:14:21.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are those whalesquid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:23.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.58,0:14:37.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed: Multiple objects \Napproaching from the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:40.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Based on the noise of \Ntheir propulsion, they are Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.62,0:14:44.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chamber, come to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.74,0:15:21.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:29.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonic wave transponder is picking up an \Nincredible number of them at 10 o'clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.52,0:15:31.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Depth approximately 30 meters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.15,0:15:32.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,30?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.89,0:15:34.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Double the number of patrol craft!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:37.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have all the escorts get up \Nto the fleet and stand by!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:39.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.23,0:15:44.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of a pod of them \Ncoming up this close to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.41,0:15:46.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How in the world do we handle this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:48.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, they'll intersect our course!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:53.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whalesquid! A whole pod \Nof them is approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.05,0:15:57.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.78,0:15:58.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.35,0:16:05.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Raise it! Raise it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.18,0:16:09.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is because we let that \Nalien on board, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:11.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:13.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please leave us be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.32,0:16:22.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.38,0:16:30.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn off the siren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.26,0:16:31.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.14,0:16:36.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take command. If you don't mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.55,0:16:39.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:40.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:46.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Fleet Commander Fairlock. \NI want you all to listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.09,0:16:49.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A pod of whalesquid is approaching the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.49,0:16:52.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a substantial number of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.57,0:16:55.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but as long as we don't make a \Nmistake, there is no danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.18,0:16:58.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As much as possible, do \Nnot stimulate the pod.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:02.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From this moment on, Gargantia is \Ngoing to power down completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.06,0:17:09.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget, relay this instruction \Nto all of the ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:12.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are to be no lights or sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:14.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:26.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After we power down, all citizens \Nstandby right where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.02,0:17:27.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make any unnecessary sounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:43.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.33,0:17:47.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Main power turning off!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.24,0:17:56.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:57.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.28,0:17:59.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:08.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't go! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.10,0:18:09.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.67,0:18:13.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! My battle has nothing \Nto do with you people!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:15.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It does have to do with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.07,0:18:16.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.21,0:18:20.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I will not make trouble \Nfor you. I will leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:21.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will fight alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:23.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:26.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to do something \Nthis dangerous! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:31.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:37.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you before. Comply with our policies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.52,0:18:38.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:40.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.06,0:18:45.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If the whalesquid attack the \Nfleet, you can do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.74,0:18:49.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But as long as they don't, I'm \Nkeeping you on a short leash.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.08,0:19:43.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're directly under the fleet right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.01,0:20:30.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.43,0:20:31.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:39.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I am here, I \Ncannot carry out my mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:42.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.45,0:20:52.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo. No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:20:57.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want Ledo and Chamber to work for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.63,0:21:03.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we team up, I'll be able to \Nsalvage from whalesquid territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.14,0:21:05.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:08.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would I be able to joke \Nabout somethin' like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:11.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They've already agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:14.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be apart from Gargantia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:15.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So sign it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:23.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, I also seek permission \Nto accompany them with my ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:28.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Flange...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.90,0:21:31.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You too? Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.38,0:21:36.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If a major ship owner like you leaves, the\N fleet's defensive capability drops sharply!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.42,0:21:40.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The legacy of a once-great age \Nis lying on the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.19,0:21:44.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can reclaim even \Na small amount of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:47.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want any hard feelings over this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.05,0:21:48.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.33,0:21:52.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never. I won't let the \Nnarrow interests of the few
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:56.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,jeopardize all of Gargantia! My answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.80,0:22:02.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.26,0:22:04.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.38,0:22:06.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Call Dr. Oldham!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.84,0:22:08.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander! {smp: this could be a double exclamation point maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.92,0:22:10.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,
